OL,3,CWhole life terms: If government wanted
OL,4,Cto change the law, they could
OL,6,FThe judge gave Rudakubana a life
OL,7,Fsentence, but said he must be jailed
OL,8,Ffor a minimum of 52 years before
OL,9,Fbecoming eligible for parole.
OL,11,FWhy - people ask? Why should the man
OL,12,Fwho cruelly took the lives of seven
OL,13,Fyear old Elsie Dot Stancombe and Bebe
OL,14,FKing, and Alice da Silva Aguiar who
OL,15,Fwas nine, and who horrified so many
OL,16,Fothers, ever get out of jail?
OL,18,FIn truth, he may never be released,
OL,19,Fbut he does have the right to seek
OL,20,Fparole from 2077.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
