OL,6,FShock at the sentence has triggered a
OL,7,Freview of it by the UK's Law Officers
OL,8,F- the Attorney and Solicitor General.
OL,9,FBut the Government has made clear
OL,10,Ftoday that it will not change the
OL,11,Frules so that minors can be subject to
OL,12,Fa whole life sentence.
OL,14,FSources point to international law,
OL,15,Farguing that it would breach the UN
OL,16,FConvention on the Rights of a Child.
OL,17,FIt states that: "neither capital
OL,18,Fpunishment nor life imprisonment
OL,19,Fwithout possibility of release shall
OL,20,Fbe imposed for offences committed by
OL,21,Fpersons beloe eighteen years of age".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
