OL,3,CWhole life terms: If government wanted
OL,4,Cto change the law, they could
OL,6,FIt is clear to me - from speaking to
OL,7,Flegal figures who have held senior
OL,8,Fpositions in Government, former
OL,9,FCabinet ministers and the types of
OL,10,Fhuman rights lawyers who would take a
OL,11,Fcase against such a decision that if
OL,12,FKeir Starmer wants to make this
OL,13,Fchange, he can.
OL,15,FYes, he would be challenged with a
OL,16,Fjudicial review that would likely cite
OL,17,Fthe UN Convention, and the European
OL,18,FConvention on Human Rights, but even
OL,19,Fif he lost that, there are ways
OL,20,Fforward.
