OL,3,CWhole life terms: If government wanted
OL,4,Cto change the law, they could
OL,6,FIn fact, I know that the previous
OL,7,FGovernment - faced with this type of
OL,8,Fcase - may well have received legal
OL,9,Fadvice that would allow them to at
OL,10,Fleast give it a go. And if they lost?
OL,11,FThey could still force through a
OL,12,Fchange in law - as primary legislation
OL,13,Fultimately trumps international law.
OL,15,FAs the barrister Isabella Kirwan told
OL,16,Fme: "The UN Convention was ratified by
OL,17,Fthe UK in 1991 but not all provisions
OL,18,Fwere incorporated into domestic law,
OL,19,Fso the Government could in theory
OL,20,Flegislate to change this."
